<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dole2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dole,</orth> subst. sorrow, grief: <cit><quote>what dreadful d. is here!</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.283" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 283</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>making such pitiful d. over them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 139</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in equal scale weighing delight and d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 13</bibl></cit>. <emph>omit we all their d. and woe,</emph> Per. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.0." default="NO" valid="yes">III Prol. 42</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>